graph.label: Action
graph.description:
An action performed by a direct agent and indirect participants upon a direct object. Optionally happens at a location with the help of an inanimate instrument. The execution of the action may produce a result. Specific action sub-type documentation specifies the exact expectation of each argument/role.

See also blog post and Actions overview document.

graph.label: ActionStatusType
graph.description: The status of an Action.

graph.label: AdministrativeArea
graph.description: A geographical region, typically under the jurisdiction of a particular government.

graph.label: AggregateRating
graph.description: The average rating based on multiple ratings or reviews.

graph.label: AlignmentObject
graph.description: An intangible item that describes an alignment between a learning resource and a node in an educational framework.

graph.label: Answer
graph.description: An answer offered to a question; perhaps correct, perhaps opinionated or wrong.

graph.label: Article
graph.description:
An article, such as a news article or piece of investigative report. Newspapers and magazines have articles of many different types and this is intended to cover them all.

See also blog post.

graph.label: Audience
graph.description: Intended audience for an item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.

graph.label: AudioObject
graph.description: An audio file.

graph.label: BroadcastService
graph.description: A delivery service through which content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

graph.label: BusinessEntityType
graph.description:
A business entity type is a conceptual entity representing the legal form, the size, the main line of business, the position in the value chain, or any combination thereof, of an organization or business person.

Commonly used values:

  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Business
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Enduser
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PublicInstitution
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Reseller

graph.label: BusinessFunction
graph.description:
The business function specifies the type of activity or access (i.e., the bundle of rights) offered by the organization or business person through the offer. Typical are sell, rental or lease, maintenance or repair, manufacture / produce, recycle / dispose, engineering / construction, or installation. Proprietary specifications of access rights are also instances of this class.

Commonly used values:

  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ConstructionInstallation
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Dispose
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#LeaseOut
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Maintain
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ProvideService
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Repair
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Buy

graph.label: Comment
graph.description: A comment on an item - for example, a comment on a blog post. The comment's content is expressed via the text property, and its topic via about, properties shared with all CreativeWorks.

graph.label: ContactPoint
graph.description: A contact point—for example, a Customer Complaints department.

graph.label: ContactPointOption
graph.description: Enumerated options related to a ContactPoint.

graph.label: Country
graph.description: A country.

graph.label: CreativeWork
graph.description: The most generic kind of creative work, including books, movies, photographs, software programs, etc.

graph.label: DataCatalog
graph.description: A collection of datasets.

graph.label: DataDownload
graph.description: A dataset in downloadable form.

graph.label: DataFeed
graph.description: A single feed providing structured information about one or more entities or topics.

graph.label: DataFeedItem
graph.description: A single item within a larger data feed.

graph.label: Dataset
graph.description: A body of structured information describing some topic(s) of interest.

graph.label: DayOfWeek
graph.description:
The day of the week, e.g. used to specify to which day the opening hours of an OpeningHoursSpecification refer.

Originally, URLs from GoodRelations were used (for Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday plus a special entry for PublicHolidays); these have now been integrated directly into schema.org.

graph.label: DeliveryMethod
graph.description:
A delivery method is a standardized procedure for transferring the product or service to the destination of fulfillment chosen by the customer. Delivery methods are characterized by the means of transportation used, and by the organization or group that is the contracting party for the sending organization or person.

Commonly used values:

  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeDirectDownload
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeFreight
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeMail
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeOwnFleet
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModePickUp
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

graph.label: Demand
graph.description: A demand entity represents the public, not necessarily binding, not necessarily exclusive, announcement by an organization or person to seek a certain type of goods or services. For describing demand using this type, the very same properties used for Offer apply.

graph.label: Distance
graph.description: Properties that take Distances as values are of the form '<Number> <Length unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 ft'.

graph.label: Duration
graph.description: Quantity: Duration (use ISO 8601 duration format).

graph.label: EducationalOrganization
graph.description: An educational organization.

graph.label: EntryPoint
graph.description: An entry point, within some Web-based protocol.

graph.label: Enumeration
graph.description: Lists or enumerations—for example, a list of cuisines or music genres, etc.

graph.label: Event
graph.description: An event happening at a certain time and location, such as a concert, lecture, or festival. Ticketing information may be added via the offers property. Repeated events may be structured as separate Event objects.

graph.label: EventStatusType
graph.description: EventStatusType is an enumeration type whose instances represent several states that an Event may be in.

graph.label: FinancialProduct
graph.description: A product provided to consumers and businesses by financial institutions such as banks, insurance companies, brokerage firms, consumer finance companies, and investment companies which comprise the financial services industry.

graph.label: GenderType
graph.description: An enumeration of genders.

graph.label: GeoCoordinates
graph.description: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

graph.label: GeoShape
graph.description: The geographic shape of a place. A GeoShape can be described using several properties whose values are based on latitude/longitude pairs. Either whitespace or commas can be used to separate latitude and longitude; whitespace should be used when writing a list of several such points.

graph.label: ImageObject
graph.description: An image file.

graph.label: Intangible
graph.description: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.

graph.label: InteractionCounter
graph.description: A summary of how users have interacted with this CreativeWork. In most cases, authors will use a subtype to specify the specific type of interaction.

graph.label: ItemAvailability
graph.description: A list of possible product availability options.

graph.label: ItemList
graph.description: A list of items of any sort—for example, Top 10 Movies About Weathermen, or Top 100 Party Songs. Not to be confused with HTML lists, which are often used only for formatting.

graph.label: ItemListOrderType
graph.description: Enumerated for values for itemListOrder for indicating how an ordered ItemList is organized.

graph.label: Language
graph.description: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in BCP 47 can be used via the alternateName property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using ComputerLanguage.

graph.label: ListItem
graph.description: An list item, e.g. a step in a checklist or how-to description.

graph.label: LoanOrCredit
graph.description: A financial product for the loaning of an amount of money under agreed terms and charges.

graph.label: LocationFeatureSpecification
graph.description: Specifies a location feature by providing a structured value representing a feature of an accommodation as a property-value pair of varying degrees of formality.

graph.label: Map
graph.description: A map.

graph.label: MapCategoryType
graph.description: An enumeration of several kinds of Map.

graph.label: MediaObject
graph.description: A media object, such as an image, video, or audio object embedded in a web page or a downloadable dataset i.e. DataDownload. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

graph.label: MonetaryAmount
graph.description: A monetary value or range. This type can be used to describe an amount of money such as $50 USD, or a range as in describing a bank account being suitable for a balance between £1,000 and £1,000,000 GBP, or the value of a salary, etc. It is recommended to use PriceSpecification Types to describe the price of an Offer, Invoice, etc.

graph.label: MusicAlbum
graph.description: A collection of music tracks.

graph.label: MusicAlbumProductionType
graph.description: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

graph.label: MusicAlbumReleaseType
graph.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

graph.label: MusicComposition
graph.description: A musical composition.

graph.label: MusicGroup
graph.description: A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.

graph.label: MusicPlaylist
graph.description: A collection of music tracks in playlist form.

graph.label: MusicRecording
graph.description: A music recording (track), usually a single song.

graph.label: MusicRelease
graph.description: A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.

graph.label: MusicReleaseFormatType
graph.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

graph.label: NewsArticle
graph.description: A news article.

graph.label: Offer
graph.description:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service — for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

For GTIN-related fields, see Check Digit calculator and validation guide from GS1.

graph.label: OfferCatalog
graph.description: An OfferCatalog is an ItemList that contains related Offers and/or further OfferCatalogs that are offeredBy the same provider.

graph.label: OfferItemCondition
graph.description: A list of possible conditions for the item.

graph.label: OpeningHoursSpecification
graph.description:
A structured value providing information about the opening hours of a place or a certain service inside a place.

The place is open if the opens property is specified, and closed otherwise.

If the value for the closes property is less than the value for the opens property then the hour range is assumed to span over the next day.

graph.label: Organization
graph.description: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

graph.label: OwnershipInfo
graph.description: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.

graph.label: PaymentMethod
graph.description:
A payment method is a standardized procedure for transferring the monetary amount for a purchase. Payment methods are characterized by the legal and technical structures used, and by the organization or group carrying out the transaction.

Commonly used values:

  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByBankTransferInAdvance
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByInvoice
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Cash
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#CheckInAdvance
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#COD
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DirectDebit
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#GoogleCheckout
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PayPal
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PaySwarm

graph.label: PerformingGroup
graph.description: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.

graph.label: Person
graph.description: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

graph.label: Photograph
graph.description: A photograph.

graph.label: Place
graph.description: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

graph.label: PostalAddress
graph.description: The mailing address.

graph.label: PriceSpecification
graph.description: A structured value representing a price or price range. Typically, only the subclasses of this type are used for markup. It is recommended to use MonetaryAmount to describe independent amounts of money such as a salary, credit card limits, etc.

graph.label: Product
graph.description: Any offered product or service. For example: a pair of shoes; a concert ticket; the rental of a car; a haircut; or an episode of a TV show streamed online.

graph.label: ProductModel
graph.description: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

graph.label: ProgramMembership
graph.description: Used to describe membership in a loyalty programs (e.g. "StarAliance"), traveler clubs (e.g. "AAA"), purchase clubs ("Safeway Club"), etc.

graph.label: PropertyValue
graph.description:
A property-value pair, e.g. representing a feature of a product or place. Use the 'name' property for the name of the property. If there is an additional human-readable version of the value, put that into the 'description' property.

Always use specific schema.org properties when a) they exist and b) you can populate them. Using PropertyValue as a substitute will typically not trigger the same effect as using the original, specific property.

graph.label: PublicationEvent
graph.description: A PublicationEvent corresponds indifferently to the event of publication for a CreativeWork of any type e.g. a broadcast event, an on-demand event, a book/journal publication via a variety of delivery media.

graph.label: QualitativeValue
graph.description: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the power cord plug type 'US' or the garment sizes 'S', 'M', 'L', and 'XL'.

graph.label: QuantitativeValue
graph.description: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

graph.label: Quantity
graph.description: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 Kg' or '4 milligrams'.

graph.label: Question
graph.description: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

graph.label: Rating
graph.description: A rating is an evaluation on a numeric scale, such as 1 to 5 stars.

graph.label: Review
graph.description: A review of an item - for example, of a restaurant, movie, or store.

graph.label: Service
graph.description: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

graph.label: ServiceChannel
graph.description: A means for accessing a service, e.g. a government office location, web site, or phone number.

graph.label: SoftwareApplication
graph.description: A software application.

graph.label: StructuredValue
graph.description: Structured values are used when the value of a property has a more complex structure than simply being a textual value or a reference to another thing.

graph.label: Thing
graph.description: The most generic type of item.

graph.label: TypeAndQuantityNode
graph.description: A structured value indicating the quantity, unit of measurement, and business function of goods included in a bundle offer.

graph.label: VideoObject
graph.description: A video file.

graph.label: WarrantyPromise
graph.description: A structured value representing the duration and scope of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

graph.label: WarrantyScope
graph.description:
A range of of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

Commonly used values:

  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Labor-BringIn
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PartsAndLabor-BringIn
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PartsAndLabor-PickUp

graph.label: WebSite
graph.description: A WebSite is a set of related web pages and other items typically served from a single web domain and accessible via URLs.

graph.label: about
graph.description: The subject matter of the content.

graph.label: acceptedAnswer
graph.description: The answer that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

graph.label: acceptedPaymentMethod
graph.description: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.

graph.label: accessibilityAPI
graph.description: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

graph.label: accessibilityControl
graph.description: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

graph.label: accessibilityFeature
graph.description: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

graph.label: accessibilityHazard
graph.description: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).

graph.label: accountablePerson
graph.description: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

graph.label: acquiredFrom
graph.description: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

graph.label: actionApplication
graph.description: An application that can complete the request.

graph.label: actionPlatform
graph.description: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

graph.label: actionStatus
graph.description: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

graph.label: actor
graph.description: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

graph.label: actors
graph.description: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

graph.label: additionalName
graph.description: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

graph.label: additionalProperty
graph.description:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

graph.label: additionalType
graph.description: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.

graph.label: addOn
graph.description: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

graph.label: address
graph.description: Physical address of the item.

graph.label: addressCountry
graph.description: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

graph.label: addressLocality
graph.description: The locality. For example, Mountain View.

graph.label: addressRegion
graph.description: The region. For example, CA.

graph.label: advanceBookingRequirement
graph.description: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

graph.label: affiliation
graph.description: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

graph.label: agent
graph.description: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). e.g. John wrote a book.

graph.label: aggregateRating
graph.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

graph.label: album
graph.description: A music album.

graph.label: albumProductionType
graph.description: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

graph.label: albumRelease
graph.description: A release of this album.

graph.label: albumReleaseType
graph.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

graph.label: albums
graph.description: A collection of music albums.

graph.label: alignmentType
graph.description: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'assesses', 'teaches', 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', 'educationalSubject', and 'educationLevel'.

graph.label: alternateName
graph.description: An alias for the item.

graph.label: alternativeHeadline
graph.description: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

graph.label: alumni
graph.description: Alumni of an organization.

graph.label: alumniOf
graph.description: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

graph.label: amenityFeature
graph.description: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

graph.label: amount
graph.description: The amount of money.

graph.label: amountOfThisGood
graph.description: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

graph.label: annualPercentageRate
graph.description: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

graph.label: answerCount
graph.description: The number of answers this question has received.

graph.label: application
graph.description: An application that can complete the request.

graph.label: applicationCategory
graph.description: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

graph.label: applicationSubCategory
graph.description: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

graph.label: applicationSuite
graph.description: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

graph.label: area
graph.description: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

graph.label: areaServed
graph.description: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

graph.label: articleBody
graph.description: The actual body of the article.

graph.label: articleSection
graph.description: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

graph.label: associatedArticle
graph.description: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

graph.label: associatedMedia
graph.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

graph.label: attendee
graph.description: A person or organization attending the event.

graph.label: attendees
graph.description: A person attending the event.

graph.label: audience
graph.description: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

graph.label: audienceType
graph.description: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

graph.label: audio
graph.description: An embedded audio object.

graph.label: author
graph.description: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

graph.label: availability
graph.description: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

graph.label: availabilityEnds
graph.description: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

graph.label: availabilityStarts
graph.description: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

graph.label: availableAtOrFrom
graph.description: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

graph.label: availableChannel
graph.description: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

graph.label: availableDeliveryMethod
graph.description: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

graph.label: availableLanguage
graph.description: A language someone may use with the item. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also inLanguage

graph.label: availableOnDevice
graph.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

graph.label: award
graph.description: An award won by or for this item.

graph.label: awards
graph.description: Awards won by or for this item.

graph.label: bestRating
graph.description: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.

graph.label: birthDate
graph.description: Date of birth.

graph.label: birthPlace
graph.description: The place where the person was born.

graph.label: bitrate
graph.description: The bitrate of the media object.

graph.label: box
graph.description: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

graph.label: branchCode
graph.description:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.

For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

graph.label: brand
graph.description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

graph.label: broadcastAffiliateOf
graph.description: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

graph.label: broadcastDisplayName
graph.description: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

graph.label: broadcaster
graph.description: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

graph.label: broadcastTimezone
graph.description: The timezone in ISO 8601 format for which the service bases its broadcasts

graph.label: businessFunction
graph.description: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

graph.label: byArtist
graph.description: The artist that performed this album or recording.

graph.label: caption
graph.description: The caption for this object.

graph.label: catalog
graph.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

graph.label: catalogNumber
graph.description: The catalog number for the release.

graph.label: category
graph.description: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

graph.label: character
graph.description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

graph.label: children
graph.description: A child of the person.

graph.label: circle
graph.description: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

graph.label: citation
graph.description: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

graph.label: closes
graph.description: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

graph.label: colleague
graph.description: A colleague of the person.

graph.label: colleagues
graph.description: A colleague of the person.

graph.label: color
graph.description: The color of the product.

graph.label: comment
graph.description: Comments, typically from users.

graph.label: commentCount
graph.description: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

graph.label: composer
graph.description: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

graph.label: contactOption
graph.description: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

graph.label: contactPoints
graph.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

graph.label: contactType
graph.description: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

graph.label: containedIn
graph.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

graph.label: containedInPlace
graph.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

graph.label: containsPlace
graph.description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

graph.label: contentLocation
graph.description: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

graph.label: contentRating
graph.description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example,'MPAA PG-13'.

graph.label: contentSize
graph.description: File size in (mega/kilo) bytes.

graph.label: contentType
graph.description: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

graph.label: contentUrl
graph.description: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

graph.label: contributor
graph.description: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

graph.label: copyrightHolder
graph.description: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

graph.label: copyrightYear
graph.description: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

graph.label: countriesNotSupported
graph.description: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

graph.label: countriesSupported
graph.description: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

graph.label: creator
graph.description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

graph.label: creditedTo
graph.description: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

graph.label: currency
graph.description: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format).

graph.label: dataFeedElement
graph.description: An item within in a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

graph.label: dataset
graph.description: A dataset contained in this catalog.

graph.label: datasetTimeInterval
graph.description: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

graph.label: dateCreated
graph.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

graph.label: dateDeleted
graph.description: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

graph.label: dateline
graph.description: The location where the NewsArticle was produced.

graph.label: dateModified
graph.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

graph.label: datePublished
graph.description: Date of first broadcast/publication.

graph.label: dayOfWeek
graph.description: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

graph.label: deathDate
graph.description: Date of death.

graph.label: deathPlace
graph.description: The place where the person died.

graph.label: deliveryLeadTime
graph.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

graph.label: department
graph.description: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

graph.label: depth
graph.description: The depth of the item.

graph.label: description
graph.description: A description of the item.

graph.label: device
graph.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

graph.label: director
graph.description: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

graph.label: directors
graph.description: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

graph.label: disambiguatingDescription
graph.description: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

graph.label: discussionUrl
graph.description: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

graph.label: dissolutionDate
graph.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

graph.label: distance
graph.description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

graph.label: distribution
graph.description: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format.

graph.label: doorTime
graph.description: The time admission will commence.

graph.label: downloadUrl
graph.description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

graph.label: downvoteCount
graph.description: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

graph.label: duns
graph.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

graph.label: duration
graph.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in ISO 8601 date format.

graph.label: durationOfWarranty
graph.description: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

graph.label: editor
graph.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

graph.label: educationalAlignment
graph.description: An alignment to an established educational framework.

graph.label: educationalFramework
graph.description: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

graph.label: educationalUse
graph.description: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

graph.label: elevation
graph.description: The elevation of a location (WGS 84).

graph.label: eligibleCustomerType
graph.description: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

graph.label: eligibleDuration
graph.description: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

graph.label: eligibleQuantity
graph.description: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

graph.label: eligibleRegion
graph.description:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.

See also ineligibleRegion.

graph.label: eligibleTransactionVolume
graph.description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

graph.label: email
graph.description: Email address.

graph.label: embedUrl
graph.description: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the src element of an embed tag and should not be the same as the content of the loc tag.

graph.label: employee
graph.description: Someone working for this organization.

graph.label: employees
graph.description: People working for this organization.

graph.label: encodesCreativeWork
graph.description: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

graph.label: encoding
graph.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

graph.label: encodingFormat
graph.description: mp3, mpeg4, etc.

graph.label: encodings
graph.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

graph.label: encodingType
graph.description: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

graph.label: endDate
graph.description: The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

graph.label: endTime
graph.description:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

graph.label: equal
graph.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

graph.label: error
graph.description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.

graph.label: event
graph.description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

graph.label: events
graph.description: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

graph.label: eventStatus
graph.description: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

graph.label: exampleOfWork
graph.description: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

graph.label: exifData
graph.description: exif data for this object.

graph.label: expires
graph.description: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. Useful for videos.

graph.label: familyName
graph.description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of an Person. This can be used along with givenName instead of the name property.

graph.label: faxNumber
graph.description: The fax number.

graph.label: featureList
graph.description: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

graph.label: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
graph.description: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

graph.label: fileFormat
graph.description: Media type, typically MIME format (see IANA site) of the content e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

graph.label: fileSize
graph.description: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

graph.label: firstPerformance
graph.description: The date and place the work was first performed.

graph.label: follows
graph.description: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

graph.label: founder
graph.description: A person who founded this organization.

graph.label: founders
graph.description: A person who founded this organization.

graph.label: foundingDate
graph.description: The date that this organization was founded.

graph.label: foundingLocation
graph.description: The place where the Organization was founded.

graph.label: free
graph.description: A flag to signal that the publication is accessible for free.

graph.label: funder
graph.description: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

graph.label: gender
graph.description: Gender of the person. While http://schema.org/Male and http://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender.

graph.label: genre
graph.description: Genre of the creative work or group.

graph.label: geo
graph.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

graph.label: geographicArea
graph.description: The geographic area associated with the audience.

graph.label: givenName
graph.description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person. This can be used along with familyName instead of the name property.

graph.label: globalLocationNumber
graph.description: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

graph.label: greater
graph.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

graph.label: greaterOrEqual
graph.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

graph.label: gtin12
graph.description: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

graph.label: gtin13
graph.description: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

graph.label: gtin14
graph.description: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

graph.label: gtin8
graph.description: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.

graph.label: hasMap
graph.description: A URL to a map of the place.

graph.label: hasOfferCatalog
graph.description: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

graph.label: hasPart
graph.description: Indicates a CreativeWork that is (in some sense) a part of this CreativeWork.

graph.label: hasPOS
graph.description: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

graph.label: headline
graph.description: Headline of the article.

graph.label: height
graph.description: The height of the item.

graph.label: homeLocation
graph.description: A contact location for a person's residence.

graph.label: honorificPrefix
graph.description: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

graph.label: honorificSuffix
graph.description: An honorific suffix preceding a Person's name such as M.D. /PhD/MSCSW.

graph.label: hostingOrganization
graph.description: The organization (airline, travelers' club, etc.) the membership is made with.

graph.label: hoursAvailable
graph.description: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

graph.label: httpMethod
graph.description: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

graph.label: image
graph.description: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

graph.label: inAlbum
graph.description: The album to which this recording belongs.

graph.label: includedComposition
graph.description: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

graph.label: includedDataCatalog
graph.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').

graph.label: includedInDataCatalog
graph.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

graph.label: includesObject
graph.description: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.

graph.label: ineligibleRegion
graph.description:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.

See also eligibleRegion.

graph.label: inLanguage
graph.description: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

graph.label: inPlaylist
graph.description: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

graph.label: installUrl
graph.description: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

graph.label: instrument
graph.description: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book with a pen.

graph.label: interactionService
graph.description: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

graph.label: interactionStatistic
graph.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

graph.label: interactionType
graph.description: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use LikeAction. For down votes use DislikeAction. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

graph.label: interactivityType
graph.description: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

graph.label: interestRate
graph.description: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

graph.label: inventoryLevel
graph.description: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

graph.label: isAccessibleForFree
graph.description: A flag to signal that the publication is accessible for free.

graph.label: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
graph.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

graph.label: isBasedOn
graph.description: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

graph.label: isBasedOnUrl
graph.description: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

graph.label: isConsumableFor
graph.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

graph.label: isFamilyFriendly
graph.description: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

graph.label: isicV4
graph.description: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

graph.label: isPartOf
graph.description: Indicates a CreativeWork that this CreativeWork is (in some sense) part of.

graph.label: isrcCode
graph.description: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

graph.label: isRelatedTo
graph.description: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

graph.label: isSimilarTo
graph.description: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

graph.label: isVariantOf
graph.description: A pointer to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive.

graph.label: iswcCode
graph.description: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

graph.label: item
graph.description: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists')’.

graph.label: itemCondition
graph.description: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.

graph.label: itemListElement
graph.description:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements. Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.

graph.label: itemListOrder
graph.description: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

graph.label: itemOffered
graph.description: The item being offered.

graph.label: itemReviewed
graph.description: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

graph.label: jobTitle
graph.description: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

graph.label: keywords
graph.description: Keywords or tags used to describe this content. Multiple entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas.

graph.label: knows
graph.description: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.

graph.label: latitude
graph.description: The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).

graph.label: learningResourceType
graph.description: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

graph.label: legalName
graph.description: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

graph.label: leiCode
graph.description: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

graph.label: lesser
graph.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

graph.label: lesserOrEqual
graph.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

graph.label: license
graph.description: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

graph.label: line
graph.description: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

graph.label: loanTerm
graph.description: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

graph.label: location
graph.description: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

graph.label: locationCreated
graph.description: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

graph.label: logo
graph.description: An associated logo.

graph.label: longitude
graph.description: The longitude of a location. For example -122.08585 (WGS 84).

graph.label: lyricist
graph.description: The person who wrote the words.

graph.label: lyrics
graph.description: The words in the song.

graph.label: mainEntity
graph.description: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

graph.label: mainEntityOfPage
graph.description: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See background notes for details.

graph.label: makesOffer
graph.description: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

graph.label: manufacturer
graph.description: The manufacturer of the product.

graph.label: map
graph.description: A URL to a map of the place.

graph.label: maps
graph.description: A URL to a map of the place.

graph.label: mapType
graph.description: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

graph.label: maxPrice
graph.description: The highest price if the price is a range.

graph.label: maxValue
graph.description: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

graph.label: member
graph.description: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

graph.label: memberOf
graph.description: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

graph.label: members
graph.description: A member of this organization.

graph.label: membershipNumber
graph.description: A unique identifier for the membership.

graph.label: memoryRequirements
graph.description: Minimum memory requirements.

graph.label: mentions
graph.description: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

graph.label: minPrice
graph.description: The lowest price if the price is a range.

graph.label: minValue
graph.description: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

graph.label: model
graph.description: The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

graph.label: mpn
graph.description: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

graph.label: musicalKey
graph.description: The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

graph.label: musicArrangement
graph.description: An arrangement derived from the composition.

graph.label: musicBy
graph.description: The composer of the soundtrack.

graph.label: musicCompositionForm
graph.description: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

graph.label: musicGroupMember
graph.description: A member of a music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

graph.label: musicReleaseFormat
graph.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

graph.label: naics
graph.description: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

graph.label: name
graph.description: The name of the item.

graph.label: nationality
graph.description: Nationality of the person.

graph.label: netWorth
graph.description: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting assets from liabilities.

graph.label: nextItem
graph.description: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

graph.label: nonEqual
graph.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

graph.label: numberOfEmployees
graph.description: The number of employees in an organization e.g. business.

graph.label: numberOfItems
graph.description: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

graph.label: numTracks
graph.description: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

graph.label: object
graph.description: The object upon the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read a book.

graph.label: offeredBy
graph.description: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

graph.label: offers
graph.description: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event.

graph.label: openingHoursSpecification
graph.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

graph.label: opens
graph.description: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

graph.label: operatingSystem
graph.description: Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OSX 10.6, Android 1.6).

graph.label: organizer
graph.description: An organizer of an Event.

graph.label: ownedFrom
graph.description: The date and time of obtaining the product.

graph.label: ownedThrough
graph.description: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

graph.label: owns
graph.description: Products owned by the organization or person.

graph.label: pageEnd
graph.description: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

graph.label: pageStart
graph.description: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

graph.label: pagination
graph.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

graph.label: parent
graph.description: A parent of this person.

graph.label: parentItem
graph.description: The parent of a question, answer or item in general.

graph.label: parentOrganization
graph.description: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any.

graph.label: parents
graph.description: A parents of the person.

graph.label: parentService
graph.description: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

graph.label: participant
graph.description: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. e.g. John wrote a book with Steve.

graph.label: paymentMethod
graph.description: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

graph.label: performer
graph.description: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

graph.label: performerIn
graph.description: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

graph.label: performers
graph.description: The main performer or performers of the event—for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

graph.label: permissions
graph.description: Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

graph.label: photo
graph.description: A photograph of this place.

graph.label: photos
graph.description: Photographs of this place.

graph.label: playerType
graph.description: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

graph.label: polygon
graph.description: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

graph.label: position
graph.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

graph.label: postalCode
graph.description: The postal code. For example, 94043.

graph.label: postOfficeBoxNumber
graph.description: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

graph.label: potentialAction
graph.description: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

graph.label: predecessorOf
graph.description: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

graph.label: previousItem
graph.description: A link to the ListItem that preceeds the current one.

graph.label: previousStartDate
graph.description: Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

graph.label: price
graph.description:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

  • Use the priceCurrency property (with ISO 4217 codes e.g. "USD") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.

graph.label: priceCurrency
graph.description: The currency (in 3-letter ISO 4217 format) of the price or a price component, when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

graph.label: priceSpecification
graph.description: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

graph.label: priceValidUntil
graph.description: The date after which the price is no longer available.

graph.label: printColumn
graph.description: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

graph.label: printEdition
graph.description: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

graph.label: printPage
graph.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

graph.label: printSection
graph.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

graph.label: processingTime
graph.description: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

graph.label: processorRequirements
graph.description: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

graph.label: producer
graph.description: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, tv/radio series etc.).

graph.label: produces
graph.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

graph.label: productID
graph.description: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789".

graph.label: productionCompany
graph.description: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

graph.label: productionDate
graph.description: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

graph.label: productSupported
graph.description: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

graph.label: programName
graph.description: The program providing the membership.

graph.label: propertyID
graph.description:
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be
(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific id of the property), or (3)
a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property (e.g. a glossary entry).
Standards bodies should promote a standard prefix for the identifiers of properties from their standards.

graph.label: provider
graph.description: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

graph.label: providerMobility
graph.description: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

graph.label: providesService
graph.description: The service provided by this channel.

graph.label: publication
graph.description: A publication event associated with the item.

graph.label: publishedOn
graph.description: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

graph.label: publisher
graph.description: The publisher of the creative work.

graph.label: publishingPrinciples
graph.description: Link to page describing the editorial principles of the organization primarily responsible for the creation of the CreativeWork.

graph.label: purchaseDate
graph.description: The date the item e.g. vehicle was purchased by the current owner.

graph.label: ratingCount
graph.description: The count of total number of ratings.

graph.label: ratingValue
graph.description: The rating for the content.

graph.label: recordedAs
graph.description: An audio recording of the work.

graph.label: recordedAt
graph.description: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

graph.label: recordedIn
graph.description: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

graph.label: recordingOf
graph.description: The composition this track is a recording of.

graph.label: recordLabel
graph.description: The label that issued the release.

graph.label: regionsAllowed
graph.description: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in ISO 3166 format.

graph.label: relatedTo
graph.description: The most generic familial relation.

graph.label: releaseDate
graph.description: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

graph.label: releasedEvent
graph.description: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

graph.label: releaseNotes
graph.description: Description of what changed in this version.

graph.label: releaseOf
graph.description: The album this is a release of.

graph.label: representativeOfPage
graph.description: Indicates whether this image is representative of the content of the page.

graph.label: requiredCollateral
graph.description: Assets required to secure loan or credit repayments. It may take form of third party pledge, goods, financial instruments (cash, securities, etc.)

graph.label: requirements
graph.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (Examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

graph.label: requiresSubscription
graph.description: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription (either paid or free). Allowed values are true or false (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

graph.label: result
graph.description: The result produced in the action. e.g. John wrote a book.

graph.label: review
graph.description: A review of the item.

graph.label: reviewBody
graph.description: The actual body of the review.

graph.label: reviewCount
graph.description: The count of total number of reviews.

graph.label: reviewRating
graph.description: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The reviewRating applies to rating given by the review. The aggregateRating property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

graph.label: reviews
graph.description: Review of the item.

graph.label: sameAs
graph.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Freebase page, or official website.

graph.label: schemaVersion
graph.description: Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. For example, a document could declare a schemaVersion using an URL such as http://schema.org/version/2.0/ if precise indication of schema version was required by some application.

graph.label: screenshot
graph.description: A link to a screenshot image of the app.

graph.label: seeks
graph.description: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

graph.label: seller
graph.description: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

graph.label: serialNumber
graph.description: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

graph.label: serviceArea
graph.description: The geographic area where the service is provided.

graph.label: serviceAudience
graph.description: The audience eligible for this service.

graph.label: serviceLocation
graph.description: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

graph.label: serviceOutput
graph.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

graph.label: servicePhone
graph.description: The phone number to use to access the service.

graph.label: servicePostalAddress
graph.description: The address for accessing the service by mail.

graph.label: serviceSmsNumber
graph.description: The number to access the service by text message.

graph.label: serviceType
graph.description: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

graph.label: serviceUrl
graph.description: The website to access the service.

graph.label: sibling
graph.description: A sibling of the person.

graph.label: siblings
graph.description: A sibling of the person.

graph.label: sku
graph.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

graph.label: smokingAllowed
graph.description: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

graph.label: softwareAddOn
graph.description: Additional content for a software application.

graph.label: softwareHelp
graph.description: Software application help.

graph.label: softwareRequirements
graph.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (Examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

graph.label: softwareVersion
graph.description: Version of the software instance.

graph.label: sourceOrganization
graph.description: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

graph.label: spatial
graph.description: The range of spatial applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a dataset of New York weather, the state of New York.

graph.label: spatialCoverage
graph.description:
The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of
      contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates
      areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

graph.label: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
graph.description:
The special opening hours of a certain place.

Use this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by openingHoursSpecification or openingHours.

graph.label: sponsor
graph.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. e.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

graph.label: spouse
graph.description: The person's spouse.

graph.label: startDate
graph.description: The start date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).

graph.label: startTime
graph.description:
The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.

graph.label: storageRequirements
graph.description: Storage requirements (free space required).

graph.label: streetAddress
graph.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

graph.label: subEvent
graph.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

graph.label: subEvents
graph.description: Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

graph.label: subOrganization
graph.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

graph.label: successorOf
graph.description: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

graph.label: suggestedAnswer
graph.description: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

graph.label: superEvent
graph.description: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

graph.label: supportingData
graph.description: Supporting data for a SoftwareApplication.

graph.label: target
graph.description: Indicates a target EntryPoint for an Action.

graph.label: targetDescription
graph.description: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

graph.label: targetName
graph.description: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

graph.label: targetUrl
graph.description: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

graph.label: taxID
graph.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

graph.label: telephone
graph.description: The telephone number.

graph.label: temporal
graph.description: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

graph.label: temporalCoverage
graph.description: The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in ISO 8601 time interval format. In the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content e.g. ScholarlyArticle, Book, TVSeries or TVEpisode may indicate their temporalCoverage in broader terms - textually or via well-known URL. Written works such as books may sometimes have precise temporal coverage too, e.g. a work set in 1939 - 1945 can be indicated in ISO 8601 interval format format via "1939/1945".

graph.label: thumbnail
graph.description: Thumbnail image for an image or video.

graph.label: thumbnailUrl
graph.description: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

graph.label: timeRequired
graph.description: Approximate or typical time it takes to work with or through this learning resource for the typical intended target audience, e.g. 'P30M', 'P1H25M'.

graph.label: track
graph.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

graph.label: tracks
graph.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song.

graph.label: transcript
graph.description: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

graph.label: translator
graph.description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

graph.label: typeOfGood
graph.description: The product that this structured value is referring to.

graph.label: typicalAgeRange
graph.description: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

graph.label: unitCode
graph.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

graph.label: unitText
graph.description: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

graph.label: uploadDate
graph.description: Date when this media object was uploaded to this site.

graph.label: upvoteCount
graph.description: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

graph.label: url
graph.description: URL of the item.

graph.label: urlTemplate
graph.description: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

graph.label: userInteractionCount
graph.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

graph.label: validFrom
graph.description: The date when the item becomes valid.

graph.label: validThrough
graph.description: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

graph.label: value
graph.description:
The value of the quantitative value or property value node.

  • For QuantitativeValue and MonetaryAmount, the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
  • For PropertyValue, it can be 'Text;', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.

graph.label: valueAddedTaxIncluded
graph.description: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

graph.label: valueReference
graph.description: A pointer to a secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature.

graph.label: vatID
graph.description: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

graph.label: version
graph.description: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

graph.label: video
graph.description: An embedded video object.

graph.label: videoFormat
graph.description: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

graph.label: videoFrameSize
graph.description: The frame size of the video.

graph.label: videoQuality
graph.description: The quality of the video.

graph.label: warranty
graph.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

graph.label: warrantyScope
graph.description: The scope of the warranty promise.

graph.label: weight
graph.description: The weight of the product or person.

graph.label: width
graph.description: The width of the item.

graph.label: wordCount
graph.description: The number of words in the text of the Article.

graph.label: workExample
graph.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. eg. The paperback edition, first edition, or eBook.

graph.label: workFeatured
graph.description:
A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent.
       Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

graph.label: workLocation
graph.description: A contact location for a person's place of work.

graph.label: workPerformed
graph.description: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

graph.label: worksFor
graph.description: Organizations that the person works for.

graph.label: worstRating
graph.description: The lowest value allowed in this rating system. If worstRating is omitted, 1 is assumed.
